# Blink Networking

## Rules

- Define events in `.blink` files under `remotes/` and `remotes/global/`
- **NEVER** edit files in `remotes/out/` — they are auto-generated by `blink`
- Run `just net` or `just dev` to regenerate after changing `.blink` files
- Main entry is `remotes/bitkaisen.blink` which imports from `remotes/global/`

## Event Pattern

```blink
event eventName {
    From: Server,          -- or Client
    Type: Reliable,        -- or Unreliable
    Call: SingleAsync,     -- or ManyAsync
    Data: (argType1, argType2)
}
```

## Usage in Luau

```luau
-- Server
local server_blink = require("@server-blink")
server_blink.account.sync.fire(player, data)

-- Client
local client_blink = require("@client-blink")
client_blink.account.sync.on(function(data)
    -- handle
end)
```

## Casing

All generated identifiers use `camelCase` (set via `option Casing = Camel`).
